“Blassgelblich, auf dem Rückenschild […] labyrinthartigen braunen Linien marmoriert” [carapace pale yellowish […] marbled with reticulate brown lines] (
Rüppell 1830: 18
). “The cephalothorax is light in colour; on some of the specimens there are irregular brown lines, which form a reticulate pattern on the cephalothorax and on the chelipeds.” (
Paulson 1875: 83
); “the dorsal surface much mottled with green and brown” (
Alcock 1896: 243
).
